args:
When ambushed by the Northern Church during
a mission, Leif is forced to enter the enemy
stronghold of Grams. But help soon arrives in
the unlikely form of Cecile, a former friend and
ally from his old Alberian days...
We have the leader of the White Sparrows\nat bay! Expand the search and bring him\nto me at once!!
(The knights of the Northern Church are\nmore tenacious that I gave them credit for.\nI never thought they'd chase me so far.)
(I only hope it gave my troops the means\nto escape, even though I should be\nworrying about my own neck right now.)
(I cannot be discovered here in Gramsâ€”\nit is the heart of the Northern Church, and\nI will never be permitted to leave it alive.)
The Holy City of Grams\nMercenary Guild Mess Hall
Goodness, dear! Slow down before you\nswallow that fool stone whole and end\nup choking to death on it.

It's not a stoneâ€”it's a Manachew. They
contain 100 percent of a body's daily
mana requirement and are a delicious
part of this nutritious breakfast.
You mercenaries take to the strangest\ntrends sometimes! Aren't you worried\nyou'll chip a tooth?

Most of us grind 'em into powder and mix
it into water. She's the only one daft
enough to call it ï¼‚Manachewï¼‚ and
eat the things whole.
Put the pebble down a sec there, lass.\nYer applying for the force the church is\nputtin' together to hit the south, yeah?

But it's such a sweet gig! Plus, ya know
they'd hire ya on, what with the way the
whole town's in love with ï¼‚Cecile the
Invincibleï¼‚ and all.
Besides, ain't you an elite from the Old\nAlberian Guard? I hear ya graduated from\na posh military school and everything.
Yeah, that's the one! You made quite the\nname for yerself there, Ms. Royal Guard.
Ms. Former Royal Guard.\nThat's all in the past now.
Still impressive as hell, though. C'mon,\nya gotta sign up with me! They'd be tickled\npink what to have ya!
Still not interested. No way in hell I'm\never going south again.
That's perfectly fine, dear. It's not like\nyou'll ever be short of work here in Grams,\nwhat with how rough it's gotten lately.
Why, just now a pack of Templars came by\nall in a tizzy about hunting down a White\nPigeon captain or somesuch.
You mean sparrows? The White Sparrows?\nBut their captain is... No. It can't be.
Where has that snake slithered off to?!
(Changing into civilian clothes may have\nbought me time, but they'll not be fooled\nby such garb for long.)
(My best chance is slipping out after\nnightfall, but I don't know the area well\nenough to plan a route.)
This would be a good deal easier if I had\na local to guide me, butâ€”
Later. Right now, shut up and stay close.
Cecile, why have we stopped in the\nmiddle of this bridge?! The enemy will\nbe upon us in moments!
On the count of ten, jump.
Just trust me. Three, two, one...
What?! \n...Wait, all of you, stop! STOP!
We're going too fast! I can't...\nNooooooo!
I can't believe you managed to time our\nleap so a ship was passing below.
That ship always passes by at that time.\nYou gotta make use of everything you can.
Oh, and...it's good to see you again.
The feeling is more than mutual, Cecile.\nHow long has it been now?
Since you were made a captain, I think.
After that, things got busy for both of us.\nNot much time for socializing.
And damn, you haven't changed a bit from\nour academy days. I recognized you the\nmoment I laid eyes.
Yes, the years have been kind to me for\nthe greater part.
Is it true what I hear about you, though?\nThat you abandoned our order and took up\nas a sellsword?
You know how rumors carry on the windâ€”\nthough I never paid them much mind.

You were always the most devoted among
all of us at the academy. When I heard
you'd renounced it all, I... Well, I didn't
really know what to think.
A lot happenedâ€”more than you can\nimagine. But you weren't the only one\nwith a little bird whispering in their ear.
I hear the White Sparrows cut free of\nDyrenell and took up with New Alberia.
Makes it even stranger to find you all\nthe way up here in the north.
We were retuning from a northern ally\nwhen we were ambushed at the border.
I broke away from my unit to give them\ntime to escape, but the Church knights cut\noff my retreat and forced me into Grams.
It makes sense to separate you given the\nthreat you could pose. Maybe those\nTemplars aren't as stupid as I thought.
They certainly have me on the back foot.\nBut fortune has favored me with our \nmeeting. Which leads me to a question...

Cecile, will you help me return home?
And what's more, as a fellow knight of
Alberia, will you fight at my side for the
royal family once more?
Please, for the sake of our old friendship,\nwill you do this thing? I can think of no\none I would rather have at my side.
A knight of Alberia... The royal family...\nFor the sake of...
No! No, no, no! No way in HELL!
